WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.041 --> 00:00:12.416
Today the police published
further information

2
00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:13.750
to Sverre Olsen.

3
00:00:13.833 --> 00:00:17.833
the perpetrator who killed
Ellen Gjelten two weeks ago.

4
00:00:17.916 --> 00:00:20.958
The deceased Olsen
was the prime suspect

5
00:00:21.041 --> 00:00:25.208
in the illegal import
of firearms to Norway.

6
00:00:25.291 --> 00:00:29.250
Agnes Sjølid. chief of police in Oslo.
explains that the investigation

7
00:00:29.333 --> 00:00:32.291
to uncover
of the criminal network continued...

8
00:00:44.958 --> 00:00:47.708
-What is that?
-Pork chops.

9
00:00:49.708 --> 00:00:50.916
Is something wrong?

10
00:00:52.666 --> 00:00:54.000
Book of Leviticus.

11
00:00:54.083 --> 00:00:57.291
Chapter 11.
No pork. no blood.

12
00:01:03.333 --> 00:01:05.000
Shouldn't be that difficult.

13
00:01:10.916 --> 00:01:11.916
You are sweating.

14
00:01:13.458 --> 00:01:17.208
I can't train today.
I cycled to Sognsvann.

15
00:01:19.541 --> 00:01:20.416
Yes?

16
00:01:25.125 --> 00:01:26.625
What are these lumps?

17
00:01:27.958 --> 00:01:30.625
That's a clean pot. isn't it?

18
00:01:33.500 --> 00:01:34.625
What does it taste like?

19
00:01:35.708 --> 00:01:36.958
Like iron.

20
00:01:42.083 --> 00:01:43.166
What the hell?

21
00:01:43.958 --> 00:01:46.125
A flood at Camilla's?

22
00:03:42.125 --> 00:03:43.125
I...

23
00:03:44.916 --> 00:03:47.708
I don't think
that you should be here.

24
00:03:52.958 --> 00:03:54.791
You know damn well.

25
00:03:54.875 --> 00:03:56.958
that I've been through this before.

26
00:03:57.833 --> 00:03:59.583
I won't do it again.

27
00:04:02.666 --> 00:04:04.541
We had an agreement.

28
00:04:06.750 --> 00:04:08.750
If that happened. it would be over.

29
00:04:12.083 --> 00:04:14.208
In that case. you should leave now.

30
00:04:19.791 --> 00:04:21.583
Isn't that what you do best?

31
00:04:23.708 --> 00:04:24.708
What?

32
00:04:44.750 --> 00:04:45.708
Yes. what's up?

33
00:04:45.791 --> 00:04:49.000
A murder case.
I need you at work.

34
00:04:52.708 --> 00:04:54.666
The thing with Ellen was difficult.

35
00:04:54.750 --> 00:04:58.791
It was hard for all of us.
but life must go on. Harry.

36
00:04:58.875 --> 00:05:00.791
I can't cover for you.

37
00:05:02.833 --> 00:05:04.833
You have to come to work.

38
00:05:04.916 --> 00:05:06.166
This is work.

39
00:05:07.500 --> 00:05:09.166
I need you sober.

40
00:05:27.041 --> 00:05:28.708
Fifth floor.

41
00:05:50.708 --> 00:05:52.083
Did you get into a fight?

42
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.333
-Do you know when...?
-The forensics are on their way.

43
00:06:13.416 --> 00:06:16.541
But she's not cold yet
or stiff. I guess...

44
00:06:16.625 --> 00:06:18.250
Probably around 5 pm.

45
00:06:19.583 --> 00:06:20.583
Why?

46
00:06:21.625 --> 00:06:23.708
The body was not moved.

47
00:06:23.791 --> 00:06:26.333
She was killed on the way
to the shower.

48
00:06:27.083 --> 00:06:29.000
Robe and corpse cover the drain.

49
00:06:29.083 --> 00:06:32.333
The janitor said.
the shower was running at full speed.

50
00:06:33.375 --> 00:06:37.750
Small bath. It didn't take long
before it flowed to the neighbors.

51
00:06:37.833 --> 00:06:40.875
The neighbor says.
they discovered it at 5:20 pm.

52
00:06:40.958 --> 00:06:43.000
That was an hour ago.

53
00:06:43.083 --> 00:06:44.958
You arrived 30 minutes ago.

54
00:06:45.041 --> 00:06:47.541
That's good. Everyone reacts quickly.

55
00:06:47.625 --> 00:06:49.875
Well. not all of them...

56
00:06:52.083 --> 00:06:55.666
I ask the janitor
if he can switch on the power.

57
00:07:03.333 --> 00:07:06.666
It already smells strong.
It's the heat and the water.

58
00:07:06.750 --> 00:07:09.375
No. I can't smell any more corpses.

59
00:07:11.791 --> 00:07:12.958
What do you think?

60
00:07:13.041 --> 00:07:16.291
Black. clotted blood
around the entrance wound.

61
00:07:16.375 --> 00:07:18.791
Soot on the skin from the shot.

62
00:07:18.875 --> 00:07:22.250
The grayish discoloration
indicates a short distance.

63
00:07:22.333 --> 00:07:23.750
Yes. I agree.

64
00:07:24.958 --> 00:07:26.500
-Do we have a magnifying glass?
-Yes.

65
00:07:35.500 --> 00:07:36.416
Everything ok?

66
00:07:37.958 --> 00:07:39.083
Yes. I...

67
00:08:04.375 --> 00:08:06.083
Well. Hole...

68
00:08:07.625 --> 00:08:09.000
Thirsty today?

69
00:08:35.791 --> 00:08:40.291
The asymmetry of the soot shows us
that the person was bigger than they were.

70
00:08:40.916 --> 00:08:42.750
He aimed diagonally downwards.

71
00:08:42.833 --> 00:08:45.333
No exit wound. the soot...

72
00:08:45.416 --> 00:08:48.250
I suspect a gun with a short barrel.

73
00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:50.875
Yes. a pistol.

74
00:08:53.375 --> 00:08:54.833
No signs of violence.

75
00:08:55.416 --> 00:08:58.791
A small swelling
in the right eye socket.

76
00:09:02.666 --> 00:09:05.375
A wire cutter
or a sharp knife.

77
00:09:05.458 --> 00:09:06.916
Do you have the finger?

78
00:09:07.000 --> 00:09:09.083
-No.
-The gun?

79
00:09:09.666 --> 00:09:11.833
-No. not yet.
-No.

80
00:09:11.916 --> 00:09:13.541
There's a lot of blood.

81
00:09:14.125 --> 00:09:17.791
Your hand is in the water.
which prevents the blood from clotting.

82
00:09:17.875 --> 00:09:21.291
But all that blood
from just one severed finger?

83
00:09:22.083 --> 00:09:23.458
That can only mean...

84
00:09:23.541 --> 00:09:26.875
That it was severed.
while her heart was still beating.

85
00:09:26.958 --> 00:09:28.458
Yes. exactly.

86
00:09:29.208 --> 00:09:32.125
They should be found.
So he left the shower running.

87
00:10:03.250 --> 00:10:05.625
-Partner?
-I don't think so.

88
00:10:05.708 --> 00:10:07.750
-No. Lover?
-Lovers?

89
00:10:07.833 --> 00:10:11.041
We are not standing there
and listen at the door.

90
00:10:12.125 --> 00:10:14.791
But you think it was a lover?

91
00:10:15.291 --> 00:10:16.916
No. I don't know.

92
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.416
I understand that.

93
00:10:18.500 --> 00:10:23.208
but those who live here would like to know
if it was personal.

94
00:10:23.291 --> 00:10:27.708
or whether there's a crazed killer running around.

95
00:10:28.291 --> 00:10:30.041
Vibeke has anxiety attacks.

96
00:10:30.125 --> 00:10:32.500
I want to teach her to live with it.

97
00:10:32.583 --> 00:10:38.500
but this fear is the dizziness
of man in the face of freedom.

98
00:10:39.708 --> 00:10:44.250
And this existential fear arises
when a person recognizes

99
00:10:44.333 --> 00:10:47.166
that he can do exactly what he wants.

100
00:10:49.916 --> 00:10:51.166
Heidegger.

101
00:10:53.041 --> 00:10:56.041
Sartre. Kierkegaard. No?

102
00:10:56.625 --> 00:10:59.208
No philosophy at the police academy?

103
00:10:59.291 --> 00:11:00.666
I am not afraid.

104
00:11:00.750 --> 00:11:02.125
Sorry.

105
00:11:04.458 --> 00:11:08.291
Maybe a mad murderer is running
up and down the stairs.

106
00:11:08.375 --> 00:11:10.875
But statistically more likely.

107
00:11:10.958 --> 00:11:14.000
that it was someone
that she rejected.

108
00:11:16.083 --> 00:11:20.375
-Do you think Camilla...
-I'm sorry. but that's completely absurd.

109
00:11:20.458 --> 00:11:25.541
I mean. your conclusion...
You know nothing about Camilla Loen.

110
00:11:25.625 --> 00:11:28.250
No. I don't know anything about Camilla Loen.

111
00:11:28.333 --> 00:11:31.125
So why do you say what you say?

112
00:11:31.708 --> 00:11:35.041
Because of 100 years of statistics
and because you asked.

113
00:11:35.125 --> 00:11:38.541
When you have finished with the questions.
may I continue?

114
00:11:40.125 --> 00:11:40.958
Good.

115
00:11:41.041 --> 00:11:44.375
Did you hear or see
someone come in?

116
00:11:47.166 --> 00:11:51.166
Is it possible
that someone has already been inside?

117
00:11:52.500 --> 00:11:53.750
Who could that be?

118
00:12:00.583 --> 00:12:04.041
-No. No?
-Not really.

119
00:12:04.708 --> 00:12:09.208
You will be summoned for questioning.
Thank you for your time.

120
00:12:19.416 --> 00:12:22.375
-Which one of you called the police?
-That was me.

121
00:12:22.875 --> 00:12:24.500
Before it was found?

122
00:12:24.583 --> 00:12:27.083
How did you know
that something had happened?

123
00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:32.291
No... Well... I cooked

124
00:12:32.375 --> 00:12:37.916
and Anders said it was like eggs.
the stuff that dripped into the pot.

125
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:42.166
Eggs curdle when they are heated.
The same happens with blood.

126
00:12:42.250 --> 00:12:44.750
If Camilla hadn't broken any eggs.

127
00:12:44.833 --> 00:12:46.666
it can only be one thing.

128
00:12:49.375 --> 00:12:50.291
Enjoy your meal.

129
00:13:17.333 --> 00:13:19.833
Hi. this is Ellen's mailbox. What's up?

130
00:13:19.916 --> 00:13:21.666
Hi. Ellen. It's me.

131
00:13:23.291 --> 00:13:26.000
I don't know what to say. but...

132
00:13:27.833 --> 00:13:29.916
I can't talk to anyone else.

133
00:13:31.458 --> 00:13:33.458
I'm after Waaler.

134
00:13:34.125 --> 00:13:35.833
He shot you.

135
00:13:36.916 --> 00:13:38.833
And I will get it.

136
00:13:40.875 --> 00:13:41.875
We promise.

137
00:13:56.416 --> 00:13:57.541
How long?

138
00:13:58.458 --> 00:14:01.541
Since the day before the hut murders.

139
00:14:03.916 --> 00:14:06.333
And why did you wait so long?

140
00:14:06.875 --> 00:14:10.333
I was a little...

141
00:14:11.791 --> 00:14:12.833
...checked out.

142
00:14:13.875 --> 00:14:18.166
Møller doesn't believe
that I know he's protecting you.

143
00:14:18.916 --> 00:14:22.333
Does he.
because you're his best cop?

144
00:14:22.416 --> 00:14:26.500
Or because he's the type
who brings stray dogs home?

145
00:14:27.666 --> 00:14:29.708
I'm not like that. Hole.

146
00:14:31.041 --> 00:14:32.000
No.

147
00:14:33.041 --> 00:14:34.000
Ok.

148
00:14:34.083 --> 00:14:35.000
Go ahead.

149
00:14:35.083 --> 00:14:37.958
While the drug squad
Sverre Olsen's garage.

150
00:14:38.041 --> 00:14:40.583
they took the photo of Tom Waaler.
when he went in.

151
00:14:40.666 --> 00:14:43.250
They didn't recognize him.
the quality was too poor.

152
00:14:43.333 --> 00:14:46.458
but as Beate Lønn.
a so-called super-recognizer.

153
00:14:46.541 --> 00:14:50.083
saw the picture.
she identified him as Tom Waaler.

154
00:14:50.166 --> 00:14:51.250
The photo?

155
00:14:51.791 --> 00:14:53.958
Yes. with 70 % certainty.

156
00:14:54.458 --> 00:14:56.958
When Ellen and I
confronted Waaler.

157
00:14:57.041 --> 00:14:59.083
he said that he wasn't there.

158
00:14:59.166 --> 00:15:01.291
He said he was home alone.

159
00:15:02.375 --> 00:15:06.500
I have spoken to the police in Stockholm
and with Interpol.

160
00:15:06.583 --> 00:15:10.250
Nobody has anything to say about Tom Waaler
from his time there.

161
00:15:10.916 --> 00:15:13.875
Do you have proof
that he wasn't at home?

162
00:15:13.958 --> 00:15:15.875
No. but it's no coincidence.

163
00:15:15.958 --> 00:15:19.583
Waaler shows up at the cabin.
where Sverre Olsen is hiding

164
00:15:19.666 --> 00:15:22.625
and where Olsen and Ellen Gjelten
were found dead.

165
00:15:23.125 --> 00:15:24.500
Is that all you have?

166
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:26.458
A coincidence?

167
00:15:27.500 --> 00:15:29.708
Let's say the picture is Tom Waaler.

168
00:15:30.916 --> 00:15:35.000
He worried and went to the cabin.
to kill Olsen so as not to testify.

169
00:15:36.541 --> 00:15:39.000
Ellen was in the wrong place at the wrong time
in the wrong place.

170
00:15:40.458 --> 00:15:43.458
She called me five times.

171
00:15:44.958 --> 00:15:49.375
Forensics found evidence of a fight
about 100 meters from the cabin.

172
00:15:52.250 --> 00:15:55.416
DNA traces from Ellen.
but nothing from Olsen.

173
00:15:57.375 --> 00:16:00.166
Her cell phone was turned off.
before she died.

174
00:16:00.250 --> 00:16:02.250
No one has seen it since.

175
00:16:04.833 --> 00:16:07.125
He tortured Ellen in the hut.

176
00:16:07.208 --> 00:16:09.833
to suggest a fight
with her and Olsen.

177
00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:18.500
This is Tom Waaler.

178
00:16:22.791 --> 00:16:27.041
This is the moment when I should
out of my office. Hole.

179
00:16:27.791 --> 00:16:29.916
Not just because you don't have a case.

180
00:16:31.166 --> 00:16:32.958
What you tell me.

181
00:16:33.041 --> 00:16:37.416
is an extreme accusation
against one of your colleagues.

182
00:16:37.500 --> 00:16:40.041
If I let you
against Waaler.

183
00:16:40.125 --> 00:16:42.875
it's my fault if you're wrong.

184
00:16:44.083 --> 00:16:45.416
You understand that.

185
00:16:49.666 --> 00:16:51.500
But even if I am right.

186
00:16:54.291 --> 00:16:55.958
But let me put it this way:

187
00:16:56.041 --> 00:16:59.416
I am extremely worried
and want to turn over every stone.

188
00:17:01.291 --> 00:17:05.708
So if you intend to
develop your theory further.

189
00:17:05.791 --> 00:17:07.250
then on your own.

190
00:17:07.791 --> 00:17:09.333
You report to me.

191
00:17:09.416 --> 00:17:10.833
Only me.

192
00:17:11.500 --> 00:17:13.750
This meeting never took place.

193
00:17:16.625 --> 00:17:19.041
Is that acceptable to you. Hole?

194
00:17:21.958 --> 00:17:23.041
It is acceptable.

195
00:17:56.208 --> 00:17:57.666
Police operations center.

196
00:17:57.750 --> 00:17:59.333
Chief Inspector Tom Waaler.

197
00:17:59.416 --> 00:18:00.958
A colleague was killed.

198
00:18:01.041 --> 00:18:03.583
The perpetrator too.
I had to shoot in self-defense.

199
00:18:03.666 --> 00:18:05.375
I'm in a hut...

200
00:18:07.125 --> 00:18:08.250
SEARCH

201
00:18:08.333 --> 00:18:10.250
NO MATCH

202
00:18:43.375 --> 00:18:46.250
Hi. this is Ellen's mailbox. What's up?

203
00:18:47.208 --> 00:18:48.958
I have found nothing.

204
00:18:50.958 --> 00:18:52.333
Nothing at all.

205
00:18:52.416 --> 00:18:53.750
He...

206
00:18:53.833 --> 00:18:57.625
I'm sure he knows I'm watching him.

207
00:19:00.125 --> 00:19:02.458
I make no further promises.

208
00:19:04.791 --> 00:19:06.375
Just like with...

209
00:19:06.958 --> 00:19:08.208
...with squeegee.

210
00:19:13.291 --> 00:19:15.791
I can't drag them into it.

211
00:19:16.625 --> 00:19:17.625
Right?

212
00:19:18.208 --> 00:19:19.625
You know that...

213
00:19:21.083 --> 00:19:22.500
You know that.

214
00:19:25.291 --> 00:19:27.541
I can't promise anything.

215
00:19:29.875 --> 00:19:32.041
I can't promise anything. just...

216
00:19:33.333 --> 00:19:34.333
I can't...

217
00:19:49.250 --> 00:19:51.333
Yes. what's up?

218
00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:53.250
Harry. where have you been?

219
00:19:53.833 --> 00:19:55.250
Or...

220
00:19:55.791 --> 00:19:57.208
I don't want to know.

221
00:19:57.291 --> 00:20:00.958
I just wanted to
remind you of Ellen's funeral today.

222
00:20:01.916 --> 00:20:03.208
Forgotten?

223
00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:06.875
No. of course not. boss.

224
00:21:45.541 --> 00:21:46.916
What are you up to today?

225
00:21:47.583 --> 00:21:49.458
I thought I'd go to Lucas.

226
00:21:50.500 --> 00:21:52.750
-We're going to the Frognerbadet.
-Good.

227
00:21:52.833 --> 00:21:53.708
Yes.

228
00:21:54.833 --> 00:21:56.791
Will Harry be back soon?

229
00:21:58.291 --> 00:22:01.000
He's busy right now. so...

230
00:22:01.083 --> 00:22:02.083
Ok.

231
00:22:03.833 --> 00:22:05.875
But I'll call you. Okay?

232
00:22:05.958 --> 00:22:07.125
-Bye.
-Bye.

233
00:22:31.458 --> 00:22:33.250
You have a new message.

234
00:22:33.333 --> 00:22:38.750
I wanted to inform you
that Harry Hole is drunk at work.

235
00:22:38.833 --> 00:22:40.583
was seen at the scene of the crime.

236
00:22:41.875 --> 00:22:45.833
-I assume you'll take care of it.
-Come on.

237
00:22:51.041 --> 00:22:52.000
Shit.

238
00:22:58.208 --> 00:23:01.333
POLICE

239
00:23:18.000 --> 00:23:19.000
Logged?

240
00:23:19.083 --> 00:23:21.833
Yes. just a moment.
I'll get you that too.

241
00:23:21.916 --> 00:23:24.666
RECIPE

242
00:23:29.625 --> 00:23:30.583
Hello?

243
00:23:39.041 --> 00:23:41.416
POLICE

244
00:23:42.708 --> 00:23:43.708
Hey.

245
00:23:46.458 --> 00:23:49.041
I am Tom. Are you Rakel's son?

246
00:23:49.583 --> 00:23:53.083
-Do you know my mother?
-She worked here when you were little.

247
00:23:53.666 --> 00:23:56.208
What... Can I help you?

248
00:23:56.291 --> 00:23:59.416
Yes. could you do Harry?

249
00:24:01.958 --> 00:24:03.375
Why does he need it?

250
00:24:03.875 --> 00:24:07.166
To get in.
when he comes home late.

251
00:24:07.250 --> 00:24:09.041
He doesn't have to sleep alone.

252
00:24:13.250 --> 00:24:15.000
You are really nice.

253
00:24:16.083 --> 00:24:17.333
But...

254
00:24:18.458 --> 00:24:20.416
You can give it to him yourself.

255
00:24:21.458 --> 00:24:23.791
He's downstairs. I'm sure he'd be happy.

256
00:24:36.333 --> 00:24:37.708
There he is. Come.

257
00:24:39.041 --> 00:24:39.875
Harry.

258
00:24:40.708 --> 00:24:41.875
Harry.

259
00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:47.958
Oleg wants to give you something. Go ahead.

260
00:24:52.166 --> 00:24:53.833
That's all right. Give it to him.

261
00:24:55.166 --> 00:24:56.416
So.

262
00:24:58.083 --> 00:25:00.000
What the hell are you looking at?

263
00:25:01.666 --> 00:25:02.583
Huh?

264
00:25:05.208 --> 00:25:07.000
What the hell are you looking at?

265
00:25:08.791 --> 00:25:10.916
What the hell are you looking at?

266
00:25:54.250 --> 00:25:55.500
Hey.

267
00:25:56.166 --> 00:25:57.083
Hey.

268
00:26:02.083 --> 00:26:03.625
Beer and bread rolls and...

269
00:26:04.958 --> 00:26:05.958
...instant coffee?

270
00:26:06.875 --> 00:26:08.083
Are you having a party?

271
00:26:09.625 --> 00:26:10.625
Yes...

272
00:26:11.416 --> 00:26:12.625
Something like that.

273
00:26:19.875 --> 00:26:21.583
There's the bull again.

274
00:26:27.833 --> 00:26:28.750
Hello.

275
00:26:52.708 --> 00:26:54.541
I have some bad news.

276
00:26:56.750 --> 00:26:58.041
Shit.

277
00:26:59.125 --> 00:27:00.541
Do you have cancer?

278
00:27:01.250 --> 00:27:04.000
No. some shit
with the stomach. Fuck.

279
00:27:04.916 --> 00:27:07.000
Slow digestion. I suppose.

280
00:27:07.083 --> 00:27:11.083
A funny expression. slow digestion.

281
00:27:11.166 --> 00:27:15.208
to digest food.
takes between 12 and 24 hours.

282
00:27:15.291 --> 00:27:18.416
no matter what.
So your intestines are not working slowly.

283
00:27:18.500 --> 00:27:21.666
it just hurts more.

284
00:27:24.833 --> 00:27:27.875
I wanted to tell you that it's over.

285
00:27:29.666 --> 00:27:30.958
Are you breaking up?

286
00:27:32.333 --> 00:27:34.666
You came to work drunk.

287
00:27:35.625 --> 00:27:39.166
I put my job on the line too often.
to save yours.

288
00:27:40.708 --> 00:27:41.916
That will stop now.

289
00:27:43.750 --> 00:27:44.708
Well.

290
00:27:54.416 --> 00:27:56.791
I have written your resignation.

291
00:27:56.875 --> 00:27:59.416
It lies on Agnes Sjølid's desk.

292
00:27:59.500 --> 00:28:02.166
The only thing missing.
is her signature.

293
00:28:08.083 --> 00:28:10.916
You don't know how much it hurts.
to see you like this.

294
00:28:33.125 --> 00:28:36.125
HEAD OF THE HOMICIDE SQUAD

295
00:28:36.208 --> 00:28:38.958
Revelation of John. chapter 16.

296
00:28:39.583 --> 00:28:43.833
"The third angel poured a bowl
over the rivers and springs.

297
00:28:43.916 --> 00:28:45.125
they became blood.

298
00:28:47.041 --> 00:28:52.083
Come. I will show you
the judgment of the great whore.

299
00:28:53.166 --> 00:28:55.250
that sits by the many waters."

300
00:28:56.583 --> 00:28:58.375
Open your eyes.

301
00:28:59.291 --> 00:29:01.541
It is a simple pattern.

302
00:29:10.500 --> 00:29:12.416
-Hello. Beate.
-Harry.

303
00:29:12.916 --> 00:29:16.666
You're on speaker.
A ballistics expert is here.

304
00:29:17.250 --> 00:29:18.500
We found the weapon.

305
00:29:19.833 --> 00:29:21.041
Oh yes. where?

306
00:29:21.125 --> 00:29:24.708
In a garbage can
near the apartment.

307
00:29:24.791 --> 00:29:26.666
You were right. A pistol.

308
00:29:26.750 --> 00:29:28.083
Brand and number?

309
00:29:28.166 --> 00:29:29.541
A Ceska.

310
00:29:30.708 --> 00:29:33.250
The serial number has been scratched off.

311
00:29:34.416 --> 00:29:36.291
What about the scratches?

312
00:29:36.375 --> 00:29:39.375
They are on all.
that we are currently confiscating.

313
00:29:40.208 --> 00:29:41.625
And the pathologist found...

314
00:29:41.708 --> 00:29:44.791
You... Take her to Waaler.

315
00:29:44.875 --> 00:29:47.791
It occurred to me.
that it was none of my business anymore.

316
00:29:50.041 --> 00:29:52.916
Okay. Let's hope that...

317
00:29:53.666 --> 00:29:56.750
...Waaler can explain the pathologist's findings
can explain.

318
00:29:58.208 --> 00:30:00.250
Yes. bye.

319
00:30:00.333 --> 00:30:01.166
Bye bye.

320
00:30:01.666 --> 00:30:02.833
No. hey...

321
00:30:03.333 --> 00:30:04.791
Wait a minute...

322
00:30:05.375 --> 00:30:06.833
Okay. well. tell me.

323
00:30:08.166 --> 00:30:12.666
Do you remember that Camilla Loen
had a swollen eyelid?

324
00:30:15.416 --> 00:30:19.875
It wasn't a swelling.
It was a small red gemstone.

325
00:30:20.583 --> 00:30:22.083
In the shape of a star.

326
00:30:25.083 --> 00:30:26.166
What do you think?

327
00:30:33.000 --> 00:30:34.666
That's none of my business.

328
00:30:36.125 --> 00:30:37.041
Good luck.

329
00:31:41.500 --> 00:31:43.041
There's the bull again.

330
00:31:44.833 --> 00:31:46.250
Where is the other place?

331
00:31:48.541 --> 00:31:49.916
Shit. the cops are here.

332
00:31:56.333 --> 00:31:58.000
Shit. the cops are here.

333
00:37:10.958 --> 00:37:13.500
Short behind the ears. please.

334
00:37:14.541 --> 00:37:16.041
Shit. it's you.

335
00:37:16.833 --> 00:37:19.375
Good. your memory
seems to be intact.

336
00:37:22.250 --> 00:37:23.208
What is that?

337
00:37:23.833 --> 00:37:27.833
A guy who came out of Sverre Olsen's garage.
before you went in.

338
00:37:27.916 --> 00:37:30.500
You realized he was a cop.

339
00:37:32.291 --> 00:37:34.041
Are you putting the scissors away?

340
00:37:36.208 --> 00:37:37.500
-Ok.
-Good.

341
00:37:37.583 --> 00:37:40.000
Roy. I'll make it easy for you.

342
00:37:40.541 --> 00:37:43.541
I'm sure you're glad
that I'm not a gangster.

343
00:37:43.625 --> 00:37:47.458
who wants to collect the drug money
that you owe. but...

344
00:37:48.208 --> 00:37:49.458
...I'm worse.

345
00:37:51.208 --> 00:37:52.916
I can arrest you.

346
00:37:53.000 --> 00:37:55.666
Then I'll arrange a raid.

347
00:37:56.666 --> 00:38:00.625
You will find the plants
that you grow in the greenhouse.

348
00:38:00.708 --> 00:38:03.166
Your mother thinks it's innocent.

349
00:38:03.250 --> 00:38:06.666
but she and your father
will be prosecuted.

350
00:38:09.958 --> 00:38:15.291
You only have to look at these pictures.

351
00:38:16.875 --> 00:38:17.916
Ok?

352
00:38:34.958 --> 00:38:36.125
No...

353
00:38:36.916 --> 00:38:39.708
I don't know who that is. but...

354
00:38:40.458 --> 00:38:41.833
I have seen him.

355
00:38:46.708 --> 00:38:48.083
He is a bull.

356
00:38:50.291 --> 00:38:51.458
How do you know that?

357
00:38:52.708 --> 00:38:56.250
Just like you. An ID band around your neck.

358
00:38:56.750 --> 00:38:59.625
You could at least hide it.

359
00:39:02.583 --> 00:39:03.750
The next picture.

360
00:39:09.375 --> 00:39:10.625
Was it him?

361
00:39:15.875 --> 00:39:18.625
Roy Kvinsvik is sure
that he saw Waaler?

362
00:39:18.708 --> 00:39:19.541
Yes.

363
00:39:19.625 --> 00:39:22.791
Good work. Hole.
We need a witness statement.

364
00:39:22.875 --> 00:39:27.541
He doesn't want to come to the station.
I meet him at the Schrøder at 11 o'clock.

365
00:39:41.625 --> 00:39:42.583
Hello?

366
00:39:49.208 --> 00:39:51.375
-Who was that?
-Nobody.

367
00:40:02.083 --> 00:40:03.166
There he is.

368
00:40:04.125 --> 00:40:08.291
Hole. this is prosecutor Abildsø.

369
00:40:09.541 --> 00:40:11.375
Yes. Harry.

370
00:40:12.333 --> 00:40:14.000
Are you alone?

371
00:40:15.625 --> 00:40:16.833
Yes...

372
00:40:16.916 --> 00:40:19.125
Roy Kvinsvik changed his mind.

373
00:40:19.208 --> 00:40:21.333
Your witness changed his mind?

374
00:40:26.958 --> 00:40:28.500
I have been thinking.

375
00:40:29.583 --> 00:40:32.416
I told you.
that it was this guy.

376
00:40:32.500 --> 00:40:34.125
because that's what you wanted to hear.

377
00:40:34.958 --> 00:40:36.875
Now you have nothing against me.

378
00:40:37.750 --> 00:40:40.166
I told my parents about the hashish.

379
00:40:40.250 --> 00:40:42.583
They burned the plants. so...

380
00:40:43.791 --> 00:40:45.416
I'm not lying for you.

381
00:40:48.375 --> 00:40:50.208
In other words. the classic mistake.

382
00:40:50.291 --> 00:40:53.500
a witness
to make a false statement?

383
00:40:56.833 --> 00:40:59.666
Potato dumplings or flank steak. what...

384
00:40:59.750 --> 00:41:03.125
I'll make it short but clear. Hole.

385
00:41:03.208 --> 00:41:06.291
I do not tolerate corrupt police officers.

386
00:41:06.375 --> 00:41:08.458
But it is my responsibility.

387
00:41:08.541 --> 00:41:11.708
the work ethic
at an acceptable level.

388
00:41:12.583 --> 00:41:14.916
The murder of Ellen Gjelten has been solved.

389
00:41:15.000 --> 00:41:16.916
The case is closed.

390
00:41:17.416 --> 00:41:21.041
If you approach the case.
that is insubordination.

391
00:41:22.750 --> 00:41:24.041
What do you say?

392
00:41:27.583 --> 00:41:28.958
Potato dumplings.

393
00:41:29.750 --> 00:41:31.250
I say potato dumplings.

394
00:41:33.333 --> 00:41:34.583
As you wish.

395
00:41:40.166 --> 00:41:41.125
Shit.

396
00:41:43.291 --> 00:41:44.458
How are you doing?

397
00:41:45.375 --> 00:41:48.666
On a scale of nine to ten: nine.

398
00:41:54.833 --> 00:41:56.250
Shit. another one.

399
00:41:56.333 --> 00:41:59.375
The forensic evidence
at the crime scene.

400
00:41:59.458 --> 00:42:04.708
that Sverre Olsen
shot and killed Ellen Gjelten.

401
00:42:04.791 --> 00:42:09.416
The investigation office
has also come to the same conclusion.

402
00:42:09.500 --> 00:42:12.041
that the police officer who arrived at the scene

403
00:42:12.125 --> 00:42:17.041
in accordance with police regulations
acted and attempted to act in self-defense.

404
00:42:17.125 --> 00:42:22.958
to save the life of a colleague.
risking his own.

405
00:45:45.083 --> 00:45:46.083
Hi.

406
00:46:05.500 --> 00:46:06.750
MANY THANKS

407
00:46:18.333 --> 00:46:20.125
Open your eyes.

408
00:46:23.750 --> 00:46:25.416
It is a simple pattern.

409
00:46:27.333 --> 00:46:29.125
A red guiding star.

410
00:46:31.375 --> 00:46:33.083
A five-pointed devil's cross

411
00:46:35.708 --> 00:46:37.000
shows you the way.

412
00:46:58.125 --> 00:46:59.583
Harry!

413
00:47:17.666 --> 00:47:18.666
Hello?

414
00:47:18.750 --> 00:47:20.416
Is there forensic evidence?

415
00:47:21.750 --> 00:47:26.541
We collected fingerprints
and DNA in the apartment.

416
00:47:26.625 --> 00:47:28.958
but nothing that fits the murderer.

417
00:47:29.541 --> 00:47:32.125
Do you know where the diamond came from?

418
00:47:32.750 --> 00:47:34.625
We are working on it. but...

419
00:47:35.125 --> 00:47:38.250
It did not come
from a Norwegian jeweler.

420
00:47:38.333 --> 00:47:41.875
This could
point to a foreign perpetrator.

421
00:47:42.458 --> 00:47:44.958
Yes. ok. Thank you.

422
00:47:45.041 --> 00:47:48.791
The last thing I heard.
was that it was none of your business.

423
00:47:49.375 --> 00:47:51.000
No. it does not.

424
00:47:52.500 --> 00:47:55.875
I dreamed of Camilla Loen
and the diamond she found.

425
00:47:56.458 --> 00:48:00.750
In the past. coins were placed
on the eyes of the dead.

426
00:48:00.833 --> 00:48:04.583
so that their souls
reach the realm of the dead.

427
00:48:05.083 --> 00:48:09.125
Yes. I know. Harry.
but I believe in science.

428
00:48:09.208 --> 00:48:11.708
I don't believe in ghosts and stuff.

429
00:48:15.041 --> 00:48:16.333
When will you be back?

430
00:48:20.458 --> 00:48:22.666
You don't believe in ghosts.

431
00:48:23.458 --> 00:48:24.541
Good night. Harry.

432
00:48:24.625 --> 00:48:25.708
Good night.

433
00:49:10.875 --> 00:49:15.000
BASED ON THE NOVEL
THE FIFTH SIGN BY JO NESBØ

434
00:50:29.000 --> 00:50:30.916
Subtitle by: Carina Chadwick
